title: gatakiriba_(ooo_combo)
body:
One of [[Kamen Rider OOO]]'s main combos, accessed via the Stag (Kuwagata), Mantis (Kamakiri), and Hopper (Batta) Core Medals.

This combo allows OOO to create [[clone|clones]] of himself like a real insect shedding its skin. These clones may attack their enemy at the same time.

He also gains access to the Kamakiri blades, in which mantis leg-shaped blades emerge from his forearm, and shoot [[electricity]] from the Kuwagata horns.

His Scanning Charge is the GataKiriBa Kick, where after splitting into several clones, OOO jumps into the air and performs a series of flying sidekicks on the target.

title: the_terminator
body:
A 1984 [[science fiction]] action film. The first film in the [[Terminator (series)|]] franchise, directed by [[James Cameron]] and starring [[Arnold Schwarzenegger]], Michael Biehn, and Linda Hamilton.

Schwarzenegger plays the [[T-800]] Terminator, a [[cyborg]] assassin sent back in time from the year 2029 to 1984 to kill [[Sarah Connor]], played by Hamilton. Biehn plays [[Kyle Reese]], a [[soldier]] from the future sent back in time to protect Sarah.

Though not expected to be either a commercial or critical success, The Terminator topped the American box office for two weeks and helped launch the film career of James Cameron and consolidated that of Arnold Schwarzenegger. 

h4. External links

title: rickenbacker_330
body:
A semi-hollow [[electric guitar]] released by American maker [[Rickenbacker]] in 1958 as part of the "300" series of guitars, which is one of their best known lines of instruments. It reached success and frequent use in a wide range of musical genres, anywhere from folk and alternative to new wave and everything in-betweem.

It is easily recognizable by its round shape, rather symmetrical cutaways, R-shaped tailpiece, simple edgy sound hole and five control kobs on post-1961 models.

Visually separate versions of the 330 include:
* [b]335S[/b], containing a vibrato tailpiece and an F-shaped sound hole.
* [b]1998PT[/b], a special 330 with an F-shaped sound hole and a triple pickup combination (similar to its older sibling the [[Rickenbacker 325]]).
* More regular-looking models with the aforementioned F-shaped hole.

title: nipako
body:
NIPAKO is the official mascot/[[personification]] of GodHand's [[ultimate nipper]], a brand of modeling nippers. Nippers are a scissor-like tool used to cut plastic parts in model making.

The project NIPAKO was closed on 31 August, 2020.

Her real name is Celine P. Nipperne. Her first design was created via [[Comipo!]] and later refined by [[Koike Satoshi]]. She also appears in the [[Ole Tower]] as a collaboration character. NIPAKO has [[long_hair|long]] [[blue hair]] with [[twintails]].

Her first upgrade is "Large" Nipako.  In this form, she carries a large, powered nipper connected by a cable to a small battery that is attached to her belt. Her attire has changed greatly, now having blue-white markings and including white [[bike shorts]] underneath her short [[skirt]].

For her second upgrade, "Ultimate" Nipako, her outfit reverts more closely to her original clothes, but with a few changes. Her top is short and sleeveless, exposing her midriff. Her equipment, which gives her a [[mecha musume]] vibe, resembles two mechanical arms with nippers.

h4. See also

title: emd_sw1
body: The EMD SW1 is a 600-horsepower (450 kW) diesel-electric switcher locomotive built by General Motors' Electro-Motive Corporation (later Division) between December 1938 and November 1953. The SW1 was the second generation of 3,402 cu in (55.75 L) switcher from EMD, succeeding the SC (cast frame) and SW (welded frame). The most significant change from those earlier models was the use of an engine of EMD's own design, the then-new 567 engine, here in 600 hp (450 kW) V6 form. 661 locomotives of this design were built, no SW1s were built after March 1943 until production started again in September 1945.

title: erica_hartmann
body:
Erica Hartmann (エーリカ・ハルトマン, Ērika Harutoman?) is a witch of the [[501st Joint Fighter Wing]], originating from [[Karlsland]]. Her familiar is the [[Dachshund]]. 

Erica is Karlsland's sixteen year old "ultra ace" of the Luftwaffe JG 52 with more than 300 confirmed victories and the rank of Flying Officer. Within the setting of the Strike Witches' world, she one of the best-seven witches in terms of shot down count. While extremely efficient and strategic in battle, Erica is rather sloppy on the ground, and her room (which she has never cleaned) is extremely messy. She is the sort of person who is only serious when the situation calls for it.

Her ace archetype is "Erich Hartmann":http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Erich_Hartmann. Erica's hairstyle is based on Erich's nickname "Bubi". She has her hair in a "Bubischnitt", which is the German term for a "bob".

title: crystal
body:
A crystal consists of matter that is formed from an ordered arrangement of atoms, molecules, or ions.  At the macroscopic scale crystals have well defined shapes with flat faces. Examples of crystals are [[snowflakes]], diamonds, and quartz.

For tagging purposes this tag is to be used for objects that are generally composed of translucent material and whose surface is composed of facets (flat surfaces).  

If it has been cut in an organized manner, particularly like that used for jewelry, then the [[diamond_(gemstone)]] tag should also be included.

If the object is rounded and features no edges between surfaces, then the object should be tagged [[gem]] instead.

For the Nuclear Throne character see [[crystal (nuclear throne)]].

title: kon_satoshi
body:
A Japanese anime director and mangaka from Kushiro, Hokkaidō and a member of the Japan Animation Creators Association (JAniCA). He was a graduate of the Graphic Design department of the Musashino Art University. His directing career includes [[Perfect Blue]], [[Sennen Joyuu|Millennium Actress]], [[Tokyo Godfathers]], [[Mousou Dairinin|Paranoia Agent]], and [[Paprika]].

Kon began work on [[Yumemiru Kikai|The Dream Machine]], but in May 2010, Kon was diagnosed with terminal pancreatic cancer. He passed away on August 24, 2010 at the age of 46. He completed storyboards and the script for The Dream Machine and left directorial tapes to Studio Madhouse to finish the film.

For tributes to Kon made by other artists after his death, see [[Kon Satoshi (director)]].

title: sagat
body:
[b]Sagat[/b] ([i]katakana[/i]: [b]サガット[/b], [i]thai[/i]: [b]สกัด[/b]) is a character in the [[Street Fighter]] series. He was originally a boss character in the early editions of series. He was later turned into a regular, playable character.

Sagat won the title of Emperor/God of [[Muay Thai]] from Nuah Kahn as a teenager, and became a national hero in [[Thailand]]. He defended his title from a fighter named Go Hibiki, in a match that cost Sagat the use of his right eye, and cost Go his life. Go's son, [[Hibiki Dan|Dan]], swore revenge on Sagat.

Sagat trained [[adon_(street_fighter)|Adon]], and held the first World Warrior tournament to prove that he was not only the strongest Muay Thai fighter, but the strongest fighter in the world. Only one fighter managed to reach Sagat: a young martial artist named [[Ryu (street fighter)|Ryu]]. Initially, Sagat was able to pin Ryu, and was sure that he was the winner of the match, even going to help Ryu up. However, Ryu became desperate to win the fight and was consumed by the Satsui no Hadou and his "[[Evil Ryu]]" side and executed the Metsu Shoryuken, grievously wounding Sagat and leaving a massive scar across his chest. Because of this event, Sagat has sworn revenge on Ryu.

He is often paired with [[Aisaka Taiga]] of [[ToraDora!]] due to the "Tiger" in his moves written and pronounced the same way as "Taiga", as well as Taiga parodying him.

title: stanley_kubrick
body:
[b]Stanley Kubrick[/b] (July 26, 1928 – March 7, 1999) was an American film director, screenwriter, producer, cinematographer, and editor who did most of his work as an expatriate in the [[United Kingdom]]. He is regarded as one of the greatest filmmakers of all time. 

His films, typically adaptations of novels or short stories, are noted for their "dazzling" and unique cinematography, attention to details to achieve realism and an inspired use of music scores. Kubrick's films covered a variety of genres, including war, crime, romantic and black comedies, horror, epic and [[science fiction]]. Kubrick was also noted for being a perfectionist, using painstaking care with scene staging and working closely with his actors.

Starting out as a photographer in New York City, he taught himself all aspects of film production and directing after graduating from high school. His earliest films were made on a shoestring budget, followed by one Hollywood blockbuster, [i]Spartacus[/i] (1960), after which he spent most of the rest of his career living and filming in the United Kingdom. 

Many of his films broke new ground in cinematography, including [[2001 A Space Odyssey]] (1968), [i]Barry Lyndon[/i] (1975), and [[The Shining]] (1980). 

While some of Kubrick's films were controversial with mixed reviews, such as [i]Paths of Glory[/i] (1957), [b]Lolita[/b] (1962), [[Dr. Strangelove]] (1964) and [[A Clockwork Orange]] (1971), most of his movies were nominated for either Oscars, Golden Globes or BAFTAs, and were later acclaimed as being masterpieces.

Widely used what is popularly known as the [[Kubrick stare]] in his films.

h4. See also

* [[2001 A Space Odyssey]]
* [[A Clockwork Orange]]
* [[Dr. Strangelove]]
* [[The Shining]]

title: dragon_breed
body:
[b]Dragon Breed[/b] is an epic, horizontally scrolling, [[fantasy]] and [[science fiction]] shoot-em-up arcade game produced by [[Irem]] (creators of [[R-Type]]) in 1989. 

In the game the player controls young King Kayus, who rides a large flying dragon named Bahamoot and battles against hordes of biomechanical monsters. Bahamoot is immune to enemy attacks, capable of blocking most projectiles and damaging enemies on contact; Kayus, however, is not, but is armed with a forward-firing energy crossbow.

Bahamoot can also spit fireballs. By holding the fire button down, the dragon will build up fire in its mouth; the longer the button is held down, the more powerful the fireball will be. There are four levels of fireball power; at its strongest, the fireball resembles a dragon's head. The game also contains some platforming elements - Kayus is able to dismount on horizontal platforms and fire his weapon from there.

Bahamoot's body is flexible and responds to Kayus' movement, enabling Kayus to use Bahamoot as a mobile shield or as a whip-like weapon. The player can also circle the tail around a group of enemies to kill them. The tail of the yellow or blue dragon can be coiled around the player to offer almost complete invulnerability for a limited time.

The original video game ran on M72 and M81 hardware, and was converted to several home computer platforms (Amiga, Amstrad CPC, Atari ST, Commodore 64, Sinclair ZX Spectrum) by Activision in 1990.

h4. See also

* [[Kayus]]
* [[Bahamoot]]

title: the_keep_(1983)
body:
[b][i]The Keep[/i][/b] is a 1983 [[science fiction]] and [[fantasy]] horror film directed by Michael Mann and starring an ensemble of actors lead by Scott Glenn, Gabriel Byrne, Jürgen Prochnow, Alberta Watson and Ian McKellen. 

Set in an ancient [[fortress]] in [[Romania]] during [[WWII]], the film deals with a group of German [[Wehrmacht]] [[soldier]]s who make [[molasar|a terrifying and deadly discovery]] inside the old keep.

It was produced and released by Paramount Pictures. The story is based on the F. Paul Wilson novel of the same name, published in 1981 (1982 in the United Kingdom).

Because of studio medling and interference the production of the film was very troubled and the final movie was both a critical and comercial failure. 

However, due to some very awesome imagery and cinematography, haunting visuals as well as an epic and enigmatic ethereal score -composed mostly of moody soundscapes- by German Electronic band "Tangerine Dream":https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Tangerine_Dream , it has achieved cult status and has become a very popular rare obscure film over the years.

title: braixen
body:
[[Pokemon]] #654 in the National PokéDex, a Fire-type Pokémon. 

It evolves from [[Fennekin]] starting at level 16 and evolves into [[Delphox]] starting at level 36. 

Braixen is a bipedal, [[digitigrade]], fox-like Pokémon. While the majority of its fur is [[yellow fur|yellow]], it has [[black fur|black]] legs, [[white fur|white]] arms, face and neck, and a dark orange tail tip. The fur on its cheeks is longer, and a small mane of white fur covers its shoulders and chest. Long, wavy [[animal ear fluff|tufts]] of dark [[orange fur|orange]] fur grow out of its large ears, and its eyes and small [[animal nose|nose]] match this fur in color. Above its legs, the fur sweeps out to either side. When its mouth is open, two pointed [[fangs|teeth]] can be seen on its upper jaw. Braixen always keeps a [[stick]] in its tail, which it sets alight using its bushy tail fur.

Japanese Name: [b]Tairenar[/b]

Prior Pokémon: [[Fennekin]]
Next Pokémon: [[Delphox]]

Formerly the home of [[Kazami Yuuka]]. [[Elly (touhou)|]] served as gatekeeper. The vampire [[Kurumi (touhou)]] lives in Lake of Blood, and is also frequently seen in the area.

An improved version of the [[Gundam Heavyarms]], made more suitable for space combat. Not many changes were made, other than the mighty Gatling being replaced by the Twin Gatling Gun for extra destructive potential. The [[Gundam Wing endless waltz|Endless Waltz]] version takes the upgrades a step further by removing the shield and knife, but adding a second set of chest guns, more missiles, and doubling up on the Twin Gatlings for a pair of them on each hand. Alternatively, the MS's colors change to a dark grey with dark green highlights. Its pilot, however, remains the stoic and collected [[Trowa Barton]].
